# Garmin integration — production hold

**Do not push Garmin Connect integration to production** unless the user explicitly says to push Garmin integration (e.g. "push garmin integration").

## Git / deploy

- Never include Garmin-related changes in routine commits, pushes, or PRs to `main`/production by default.
- When the user asks to commit or push other work, **exclude** Garmin files unless they explicitly include Garmin in that request.

## Garmin-related paths (hold from production)

Garmin code is **not in the repo** until explicitly re-added. When re-implementing, exclude from routine pushes:

- `src/lib/garmin.ts`, `src/lib/garmin-sync.ts`
- `src/app/api/garmin/**`
- `prisma/migrations/*garmin*`
- `GarminAccount` schema
- Garmin env vars (`GARMIN_CLIENT_ID`, `GARMIN_CLIENT_SECRET`)

## Allowed without explicit Garmin push approval

- Manual wellness logging and recovery readiness **without** Garmin auto-sync
- Strava and other non-Garmin features
- Local development of Garmin code on a feature branch

## When user says "push garmin integration"

Only then: commit Garmin changes, push to remote, deploy, and document Garmin env + webhook setup for production.
